posts.post_content:
@DarthParallax:  

When you remove the last time counter from a suspended card, you cast it without paying its mana cost. So the opponent can counter it like any other spell. They can also use [Nix](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Nix) on it. Actually, the Future Signt [Pact](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pact)s and cards with suspend were the reason for [Nix](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Nix)'s existence.  

As for [Rift Bolt](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rift Bolt) itself, it's a perfect addition for red storm decks. Moreover, as has already been mentioned, by suspending it, you can quite often delay your opponent from casting a creature for a turn, which can be a really useful tempo advantage if you 're trying to combo FTW or if you're playing a con-trolling deck (pun intended).

